  <amendments/>
  <summary>3/5/1997--Introduced.
Prohibits U.S. assistance to Mexico for FY 1998 unless the President determines and certifies to the Congress by September 1, 1997, that the Government of Mexico meets specified narcotics control requirements. Directs the Secretary of the Treasury to instruct the U.S. Executive Director of each multilateral development bank to vote against any loan or other funds utilization for Mexico for 1998 if the President does not so certify by the deadline.</summary>
